  President Muhammadu Buhari has urged Nigerians to ensure that the 2023 general election is peaceful in honour of the late winner of the annulled June 12, 1993 presidential election, the late Chief MKO Abiola, and other heroes of democracy.In his Democracy Day speech, Buhqri said, “It is important for all of us to remember that June 12th, 2023 will be exactly 30 years from the 1993 Presidential elections. In honour and memory of one of our national heroes for democracy, Chief M.K.O Abiola, GCFR, we must all work together to ensure this transition is done in a peaceful manner.”